From a36af408887cb0c12b1d685ba19d3af6d50043f1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Neale <michael.neale@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 08:54:14 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 04/07] MoE Phase 1: expert mask routing + analysis tool

Phase 1a: moe-analyze tool
- Intercepts ffn_moe_probs via eval callback to observe router decisions
- Computes per-expert gate mass, selection counts, concentration stats
- Simulates group masking across different group counts (2/4/8) with replicas
- Result: 99.3% routing mass capture even at 8 groups (16 experts/group)

Phase 1b: expert masking during inference
- llama_model_set_expert_mask() public API to set/clear expert masks at runtime
- llm_graph_input_expert_mask input class with set_input pattern
- Mask applied in build_moe_ffn() as -inf additive bias before argsort_top_k
- Shared mask tensor across all MoE layers (created lazily on first layer)
- expert_mask_enabled + fixed-size bool array in hparams (trivially copyable)

Phase 1b results on Qwen3-30B-A3B (128 experts, top-8, 4 groups of 32):
- Best group: -0.105 avg logprob delta (nearly lossless)
- Worst group: -2.292 avg logprob delta (significant degradation)
- Key finding: routing mass capture != quality preservation
- Validates probe-based session placement approach
